Don’t get lobbed 🫵🏻

One of the most painful ways to concede 🫠

@starstoppersgk with the drill here to try and train the GK into getting back both balanced and with speed 🧤

• Start on the floor facing the feeder
• Trigger
• Sprint to feeder and touch ball
• Back track angled keeping eyes on ball
• Attempt the save
• Reset

🚨The Value🚨

It’s important to stay balanced whilst judging the trajectory of the ball, do this by retreating like @thebigcatgk does in the drill shown. When you think you are in a position that you can affect the ball that’s when you dive for it. Land safely GKs 🧤

Drill 👉🏻 @starstoppersgk 
GK 👉🏻 @thebigcatgk

Come and affect it 🫵🏻

🚨The set up🚨
👉🏻 Make it match relevant 🫵🏻

• Start off your line as if your team mates were holding the free kick line on the edge of your 18.
• Have the ball clipped into an area (varied heights, power and distances from you)
• Come and affect it if you can
• Distribute back to the feeder

This is a drill where you are learning through trial and error. Every ball flight is different and the picture in front of you is constantly changing. 

Some balls catch… some will be better to punch… and some leave and hold the best position in your goal.
You decide how you are going to affect the ball 🫵🏻
Do 5 reps… pause and share feedback with the feeder.

Go and enjoy this one GKs 🧤

Serious value down here 👇🏻

They are spinny, horrible.. bounce right in front of you and can be an absolute nightmare to deal with.

The drill
• Face the side line
• Trigger
• Turn head then body toward striker
• Half volley strike
• Adjust position 
• Make save
• Reset

Ultimately you will have to use every save in your Arsenal to deal with this type of shot… in the reel there were three different trajectories to deal with and each one had a different solution 👉🏻 (dive/scoop/scoop collapse)

🚨The Value🚨

Footwork is what is going to get you out of trouble here small adjustments to get the ball back in line with your body when attempting a scoop or those little half steps to get you closer before you dive.
Keep your eyes on the ball at all times and pay particular attention when the ball bounces in front of you, any amount of spin or uneven ground can change the trajectory, being as in line as you can before that bounce will give you the best chance of making that save.

Massive value down here 👇🏻👇🏻👇🏻

The collapse save is a staple in any goalkeepers arsenal, it will be your go to save for mid to long range strikes.

The technique
• Drive forward to meet the ball
• 3 points of contact (hand/ground/hand)
• Secure that ball

🚨The value🚨

Variations on feed

For a ground collapse
• Rolled out
• Ground strike (as seen in drill)

For a mid collapse
• Thrown
• Volley
• Half volley
• Ground strike

Variations on the footwork

• work up and down the ladder
• work each side of the ladder
